Every day he cut down the trees
He would burn them and make black coals and sell them
One day a lost horseman reached the forest
Tired and exhausted, the horseman asked Takshaka for water
It was about noon
So Takshaka offered his food to the hungry guest and gave him water
Satisfied with the food the rider introduced himself
The traveler was the king of the side kingdom
After taking some rest, the king thanked Takshaka and told him
If you ever get in trouble, please remind me
I will definitely help
You can come to me whenever you want
In time he cut down all the trees in the forest
Takshaka made black coals by burning them and selling them
The forest is finished
Takshaka became worried
Next came the question of how to earn money
Suddenly he remembered the king
So he reached the capital and met the king and told him about his problem
The king gave his sandalwood forest protected outside the great city to Takshaka
A few months later the king remembered Takshaka
He went to the forest to find out his condition
There were two trees left
After they were finished, Takshaka, with a pale face, began to cry, wondering what had happened
The king was astonished to see this
He wondered where the sandalwood trees had gone
Asked by the king, Takshaka replied
I continued to make and sell black coals as before
That he did the same here
The king, knowing his ignorance, laughed to himself
Cut down a branch of the sandalwood tree and go to the market and sell it and come back
He ordered him to send Takshaka to the market
Seeing a piece of sandalwood in the market
Shops willing to buy have arrogantly increased prices
He sold sandalwood for about ten thousand rupees
Takshaka got so much money and realized how much sandalwood was worth
Remembering that until today only sandalwood wood had been burnt to make charcoal, Takshaka felt great regret
