Storyteller Dr. Kamlesh Kumar
In a certain forest there lived four affectionate rabbits, snakes, turtles and foxes
Once some discussion ensued among them
The discussion raised the issue of what we should do if this forest is suddenly set on fire
All four presented the topic according to their own views
The hundred-minded rabbit said I am in a hundred ways to examine my face to enter the cave when the forest is on fire
That there is no other way
The thousand-minded snake said, "My opinion is that of climbing a tree
When the forest is on fire, we should all climb trees
Not that you have to go anywhere else
So said the crocodile tortoise with the natural armor
said the unanimous fox, who sat listening to the opinions of all three
Friends, I definitely have only one opinion
That if the forest is on fire, one must leave the forest and flee elsewhere
Everyone entered their respective residences expressing their own opinions
Then one day a forest fire broke out in the forest
The rabbit entered the cave
And the fox, following his opinion, fled out of the forest
The days have passed
The first thing he did was come to the rabbit's den
There was a hundred-minded rabbit burnt to death in the fire
Then the tree was observed
A thousand-minded snake hanging there came into view like a burnt rope
The tortoise, who had thought for a million times and was engaged in action, appeared like golden coal on the ground
Seeing all this heartbreaking scene the fox left sadly
